==Games==
;Oresama Quest (おれさまクエスト)
Oresama Quest was a PC game released June 23, 2006.<ref>http://www.twofive.co.jp/maoh/index.html</ref>

;Hajimari no Tabi (はじマりの旅)
Hajimari no Tabi was a PS2 action RPG video game developed and published by Namco Bandai. It was released in Japan on July 27, 2006. There were two versions released. The normal game and a premium box which included a drama CD and a booklet with an original story by Takabayashi Tomo.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://maoh.namco-ch.net/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023155210/http://maoh.namco-ch.net/ |archive-date=2014-10-23 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

;Shin Makoku no Kyuujitsu (眞マ国の休日)
Shin Makoku no Kyuujitsu was a PS2 game released September 27, 2007. There were two versions released. The normal game and a limited box which included two figures, a script book and a drama CD.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://maoh.namco-ch.net/shinmakoku/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509194831/http://maoh.namco-ch.net/shinmakoku/ |archive-date=2013-05-09 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

