{{italic title}}
[[File:GUGG Still Life Flowers.jpg | thumb]]
'''''Still Life: Flowers''''' ('''''Nature morte: fleurs''''') is an oil on canvas by Pierre Auguste Renoir in the Thannhauser Collection at the Guggenheim Museum, New York.    

This 1885 painting is similar to ''Still Life: Flowers and Prickly Pears'' believed to be painted a year earlier, but Renoir did not include the fruit and table cloth, plus was more restrained in the color. <ref>{{cite book|last1=Barnett|first1=Vivian Edicott|last2=Krens|first2=Thomas|title=Guggenheim Museum Thannhauser Collection|publisher=The Solomon R. Guggenheim Foundation|location=New York|isbn=0-89207-074-9}}</ref>

