{{Pierre-Auguste Renoir}}

[[Category:1885 paintings]]
[[Category:Paintings by Pierre-Auguste Renoir]]
[[Category:Still life paintings]]

'''Pieter Arnout Dijxhoorn''' (1810–1839), a Dutch [[Marine art|marine painter]], was born at [[Rotterdam]] in 1810. He was a scholar of [[Martinus Schouman]] and of [[Johannes Christiaan Schotel|J. C. Schotel]], and painted marine subjects and river scenes in an able manner. He died at Rotterdam in 1839.

